type ChannelSuiteBase ¶

Embed into other suite types to have a connection and channel automatically set up for testing on suite start, and closed on suite shutdown. 

type ChannelSuiteBase struct {
    suite.Suite

    Opts *ChannelSuiteOpts
    // contains filtered or unexported fields
}

func (*ChannelSuiteBase) CreateTestExchange ¶ 

func (suite *ChannelSuiteBase) CreateTestExchange(name string, kind string)

func (*ChannelSuiteBase) CreateTestQueue ¶ 

func (suite *ChannelSuiteBase) CreateTestQueue(
    name string, exchange string, exchangeKey string,
) amqp.Queue

Creates a basic test queue on both test channels, and deletes registers them for deletion at the end of the test. The created queue can be optionally bound to an exchange (which should have been previously created with CreateTestExchange).

func (*ChannelSuiteBase) GetMessage ¶ 

func (suite *ChannelSuiteBase) GetMessage(
    queueName string, autoAck bool,
) dataModels.Delivery

get a single message, failing the test immediately if there is not a message waiting or the get message fails.

func (*ChannelSuiteBase) PublishMessages ¶ 

func (suite *ChannelSuiteBase) PublishMessages(
    t *testing.T, exchange string, key string, count int,
)

Published messages on the given exchange and Key, waits for confirmations, then returns. Test is failed immediately if any of these steps fails.
